This paper is about using a D-Wave quantum annealer for unsupervised machine learning, specifically nonnegative binary matrix factorization. The paper discusses using this method to learn facial features from a set of images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.ET (Emerging Technologies).
